OL,3,CConcern over the state of local roads
OL,4,Creaches record high
OL,6,FA report by the Whitehall spending
OL,7,Fwatchdog the National Audit Office,
OL,8,Fpublished last month, found the
OL,9,FGovernment has "significant gaps" in
OL,10,Fits understanding of the quality of
OL,11,Froad surfaces.
OL,13,FClaire Holland, transport spokesperson
OL,14,Ffor the Local Government Association,
OL,15,Fwhich represents councils in England
OL,16,Fand Wales, said: "Limited resources
OL,17,Fand a #16.3 billion local roads repair
OL,18,Fbacklog means councils have had to
OL,19,Fprioritise road repairs according to
OL,20,Flocal circumstances."
